Bushwick Ave., south from Maujer Street. No. 126 Bushwick Ave., is the empty lot at the right foreground, with billboards.

Bushwick Ave., east side, from Maujer to Ten Eyck Streets. A view of St. Catherine's Hospital. In the foreground, are razed buildings, making way for the new F.H.A. apartments.
December 22, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, a close-up of St. Catherine's Hospital. In this view Maujer Street is in the foreground.
December 22, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

Maujer Street, to the south westward from Bushwick Ave., showing block after block of razed buildings, to make way for new apartments under the Federal Housing Administration. Also at the left, are seen the steeples of the R. C. Church of the Most Holy Trinity.

December 22, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
